snippet.title: Best digital cameras
snippet.description: Here's where you find the best of the best, our top digital cameras across the board.

snippet.title: Vice President Biden joins Instagram
snippet.description: The official account appears to be managed by staffers, but one can still wish for an image slip-up or two.

snippet.title: YouTube vice president touts paid subscriptions
snippet.description: The online video site sees paid subscriptions as a way to generate more revenue for content creators but remains mum on specific details.

snippet.title: NAB president to FCC: Stop favoring broadband
snippet.description: President and CEO of the National Association of Broadcasters Gordon Smith takes the FCC to task for its policies he said favor broadband over the broadcast industry. And he called on the Commission to come up with a National Broadcast Plan.

snippet.title: Paul Graham steps down as Y-Combinator president
snippet.description: The Silicon Valley leader taps Y-Combinator alum Sam Altman to take over as president of the startup incubator.

snippet.title: PayPal President David Marcus and The Wrath of Cant
snippet.description: David Marcus may not have endeared himself to some of those who work for him in San Jose, Calif., by admonishing them if they don't use PayPal apps.

snippet.title: Hillary Clinton tells tech audience: I'm thinking of running for president
snippet.description: She's not an official candidate for the 2016 run for the White House, but the former Secretary of State sounds as if she's close to stepping into the ring.

snippet.title: Meet the (wo)men who could be named Intel's next CEO
snippet.description: CNET details the pluses and minuses for some candidates, including Intel Chief Operating Officer Brian Krzanich and VMware CEO Pat Gelsinger.

snippet.title: Acer's financial woes force exit of CEO, president
snippet.description: The company's founder takes over as chairman and interim president as J.T. Wang and Jim Wong give up their positions, effective immediately.

snippet.title: A closer look at the Microsoft insiders who didn't get the job
snippet.description: Satya Nadella wasn't the only Microsoft insider on the CEO shortlist. What's next for Tony Bates, Kevin Turner, and Stephen Elop now that they didn't get top spot?
